<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Preferably through the command line. I need this in order to incorporate it with dunst&#39;s pause feature. I am using this to make use of a DND (Do-Not-Disturb) module in my polybar. While setting paused to true through dunst does in fact hide all notifications received in that period, notification sounds from apps still come through - for example Discord (but any and all apps for that matter) </p> <p>For context, I am using bspwm and <a href="https://github.com/beyond9thousand/dotfiles/blob/bspwm/.config/bspwm/bspwmrc">this</a> is my autostart file (bspwmrc)</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/beyond9thousand"> /u/beyond9thousand </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wb8a0l/how_to_mute_notification_sounds_in_the_absence_of/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wb8a0l/how_to_mute_notification_sounds_in_the_absence_of/">[comments]</a></span>